The paper deals with natural language processing and database schemas, which are relevant to the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), databases (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of neural encoder-decoder paradigm and self-attention mechanisms are also common in these sub-fields. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
